FBIS3-14702 "drnes061_l_94008" FBIS-NES-94-061 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 ISRAEL Chief of Staff Affirms IDF `Duty' To Enforce Law TA2903182594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 29 Mar 94 TA2903182594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] Touring the Gaza Strip today, Lieutenant General Ehud Baraq, the chief of staff, said it is the IDF's [Israel Defense Forces] supreme duty to enforce law and order on Arabs and Jews alike. He further said that to foil terrorist attacks, officers and soldiers have to be alert and vigilant. An instant reaction by a soldier who finds himself on the scene of an attempted attack can make all the difference between a successful or a foiled attack. Our correspondent Karmela Menashe reports that the chief of staff inspected the preparations for the implementation of the Gaza-Jericho agreement.
